WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.800
As our learners work through assignments, it can be helpful to check on their progress,

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:13.280
as well as see their code in a working environment in order to help them troubleshoot any issues

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:14.280
that they're having.

00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:18.320
And we can do all of that from within RStudio Cloud.

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:23.520
For this walkthrough, I've added myself as a learner to our data visualization workspace,

00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:27.200
which we can confirm by clicking on the Members tab.

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:29.879
There are two ways to access learner work.

00:00:29.879 --> 00:00:33.320
One is to click on an individual's name from the Members tab.

00:00:33.320 --> 00:00:36.840
When we do this, we're taken to our learner's projects.

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:41.080
In this case, our learner has only worked on assignment 1, but we can click into their

00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:45.680
work and see what they've created, as well as run their code.

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:49.759
It's important to note that when we open a learner's project in RStudio Cloud, we are

00:00:49.759 --> 00:00:52.680
not creating a separate copy of their work.

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:55.360
We're directly accessing their work.

00:00:55.360 --> 00:00:59.639
Any changes we make here will be incorporated into the learner's project.

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:04.480
One advantage of this is that we can write comments or provide example code for our learners

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:07.279
in an asynchronous manner.

00:01:07.279 --> 00:01:11.199
Another point worth mentioning is that if we as educators, or really anyone with the

00:01:11.199 --> 00:01:16.239
moderator or administrator role within the workspace, opens a learner's work while the

00:01:16.239 --> 00:01:21.120
learner is working on it, the learner will be disconnected from their project.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:25.000
It may be helpful to let learners know that this may happen, especially if you and your

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.000
learners are working asynchronously.

00:01:29.639 --> 00:01:31.800
♪AT&T jingle♪

